reviews.review_text: Head(phone) Candy! Dusborne has done it again! Lovely matrix, powerful performance! This is a perfect matrix to my ears.  Super wonderful versions of 'Loser' and "Stella Blue'. And, of course, the amazing return of the legendary "Mind Left Body" jam that was explored during '73 & '74.  Brent's playing on this jam and elsewhere during the show and tour is astonishing.  Thanks, Dave!
good stuff Jerry is strong, people are really getting exited during the solo in Loser. good stuff

Great Matrix of a Sick Show! It's great to be able to stream again since they were taken down as parts of these shows were featured on Dozin' & W/O a Net. It must be Christmas!!! Possibly the greatest 3 day run of the Brent era - up there with Alaska '80, Alpine '89 and the Nassau and April Fools runs from this tour

Superb Sound I just listened to a few songs and I'm writing this review.  Simply superb sound, and what I like is you get the stadium / arena feel of the concert (appropriate crowd noise) along with the crispness of having an SBD.  

I haven't listened to other copies.  Part of this show is already officially distributed as Dozin' and the Spring 1990 Box Set (as filler material).

Despite this, I will probably listen to this version.  Stunning!

Oh and by the way, Loser is everything that people say it is.

WHHHOOOOOSHHHH!!! Boyoboy, Dave, what you can do with good material. You REALLY manage to capture levels of a show's emotional journey in your mixes. Everything is so clean here, subtle, presence and balances so well-thought-- and have a way of nailing the EQ every time. Since EVERY Head will ALWAYS start fiddling with their home system's EQ anyway, you seem to always provide a fine, very listenable baseline. 
Thank you.
Excellent MTX, very well mixed The show, while somewhat overrated, is still very good.
